SCHEMA NOTES

limit_ambiguous: If limit_value is 0 and the actual deadline is genuinely
unknown or disputed across sources, set limit_ambiguous to true. A zero
limit_value with limit_ambiguous false implies the deadline is verifiably
zero — use this only when that is literally correct.

burden_of_proof_flag: Omit this field entirely unless a meaningful or
non-standard burden shift is identified for this statute. Do not include
it as false by default.

url_source: Populate with the domain name only (e.g., "legiscan.com",
"law.justia.com"). Omit when is_official is true or when no URL is present.

